metadata.name: SMPTE-V2
metadata.description: SMPTE timecode (/ˈsɪmptiː/ or /ˈsɪmtiː/) is a set of COOPERATING standards to label individual frames of video or film with a timecode. The system is defined by the Society of Motion Picture and Television Engineers in the SMPTE 12M specification. SMPTE revised the standard in 2008, turning it into a two-part document: SMPTE 12M-1 and SMPTE 12M-2, including new explanations and clarifications.
